Author: TwilightPunkster K64#7533
Content:
```Komodo educational academy```
Welcome to Discord. The academy here old school. Spartan. Sorry, it's rtfm. Learned that the hard way. When you understand that part, you seek a trainer. Like Tony the Barbarian, Siu The Great, Regnar the Wise, Paladin Fishy. Be careful of that 777 dude, he's like Zeus shooting thunderbolts and stuff.
```other educational content creation,```
That's DIY, the hacker way. And when you get something working nifty, you get fancy green on you with "Ecosystem Developer" 
```case studies```
Tech Tuesday, Five Bullet Friday, Ecosystem Spotlight, Wha-wha-wha-white-paypas.
```Tie up with blockchain educational platform such as blockgeeks ```
Careful, pioneers, makers of chains, chameleons, cakeshoppers, gamedevs roam here!
```Announcing Grants for cool project build on komodo```
Like Unreal Engine grant applications? Nope, don't happen around here!
```organising meetups and events```
High on the clouds the two Barts live. They have bar, called Blockbar. We drink beer there. No meetups. No events. Only co-working and expo's.
```Using podcast and other mediums to tell what happening inside komodo```
You probably missed Bitcoin Benny. He's like Oprah, only more handsome and more interesting.
```Working with Infra companies such as digital ocean, heroku to provide asset chain templates ```
Does Amazon as technology partner say something? 
```dev documentation designed to get started various things```
A developer that can't read the markup on GitHub and doesn't understand Python, should probably start to learn programming first prior calling themselves a developer.... (unless its business developer, but those are scared of GitHub)
```Reaching out to developer and find ways to train them```
Certain people who are nicknamed the machine will train any decent willing, brave student up to speed in two weeks.
